
[1]parallax

   PAR'ALLAX, n. [Gr. to vary, to decline or wander; beyond, and to
   change.] In astronomy, the change of place in a heavenly body in
   consequence of being viewed from different points.

   Diurnal parallax, the difference between the place of a celestial body,
   as seen from the surface, and from the center of the earth, at the same
   instant.

   Annual parallax, the change of place in a heavenly body, in consequence
   of being viewed at opposite extremities of the earth's orbit.
